 For example, a keiretsu bank would not finance an entry into the market by a competitor of one of its associated companies; 
a trading company will not help import products of competitors; and a foreign company will be unable to develop a distribution 
network. In short, keiretsu constitute a substantial barrier to foreign entry into the Japanese market.
